The paper deals with scientometrics, which is a subfield of computer science that deals with the quantitative analysis of scientific research. The paper specifically focuses on the co-authorship and citation networks of a scientific community, which falls under the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SI) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The analysis of the preferential attachment function and author fitnesses involves statistical modeling and estimation, which falls under the sub-category of statistical computing (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the competitiveness and competency of authors, which falls under the sub-categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and systems and control (cs.SY).
